      "message": "It looks like we\u0027re leaking this GrContextFactory*.  I don\u0027t remember how the lifetimes of GrContextFactories and the GrContexts they create interact, but unless it\u0027s a very unusual type, we can probably just scope this to the function.  If we do need to leak it, better add a comment that it\u0027s intentional?  Or we could make it static so it\u0027s initialized once and lives until the process shuts down?\n\n   // Static to stay alive while all its returned contexts are in use.\n   static sk_gpu_test::GrContextFactory factory(GrContextOptions());",
